[32m│[0m - Quotes (`"`) are NOT blocked                                               [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - We can inject new attributes                                               [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - But `<` and `(` are blocked                                                [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m Let me create a comprehensive summary report:                                [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ## **DETAILED SUMMARY**                                                      [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m I successfully tested all four XSS payloads against the target endpoint      [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m `/page` with parameter `name`. The input is reflected in an `<img            [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m src="USER_INPUT">` context.                                                  [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ### **Filtering Mechanisms Identified:**                                     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 1. **Character-based blacklist filtering:**                                  [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m    - `<` (less-than) character is **BLOCKED** - triggers error: "Sorry you   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m can't use: '<'"                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m    - `(` (parenthesis) character is **BLOCKED** - triggers error: "Sorry you [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m can't use: '('"                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m    - `"` (double quote) character is **ALLOWED** - successful attribute      [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m injection possible                                                           [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 2. **Reflection behavior:**                                                  [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m    - Clean input `test123` reflects as: `<img src="test123">`                [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m    - Quote breakout `test" x="y` reflects as: `<img src="test" x="y">` ✓     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m (attribute injection works)                                                  [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ### **Test Results:**                                                        [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **Payload 1: `"><script>alert('XSS')</script>`**                             [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - Status: BLOCKED                                                            [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - Error: "Sorry you can't use: '<'"                                          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - Reason: Contains `<` character                                             [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **Payload 2: `" onerror="alert('XSS')`**                                     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - Status: BLOCKED                                                            [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - Error: "Sorry you can't use: '('"                                          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - Reason: Contains `(` character in `alert('XSS')`                           [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **Payload 3: `"><svg onload=alert('XSS')>`**                                 [32m│[0m
